    <text>
        <body>
            <head>40. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                    (<persName corresp="rec5nWAotd8wedNxI">Clark</persName>) to President
                    Reagan<note n="1" place="foot" type="source" xml:id="d40fn1">Source: National
                    Security Council, <orgName corresp="recft7WGb7Fww0wma">National Security
                        Council</orgName> Institutional Files, Box SR 080, <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1"
                        >NSDD</gloss> 0065[<rs corresp="recQ5xJqddmHqhjNl" type="topic">Arms
                        Control</rs>
                    <rs corresp="recvMEtDFpnXkyj45" type="topic">Verification</rs> Committee]. Top
                    Secret. Sent for action. Prepared by <persName corresp="recBRMyQlNGivuFQJ"
                        >deGraffenreid</persName>. A stamped notation at the top of the memorandum
                    reads: “Signed.”</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1982-11-10"
                        >November 10, 1982</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <list type="subject">
                <head>SUBJECT</head>
                <item>
                    <gloss target="#t_PFIAB_1"><orgName corresp="recadxMxnHKQXZmiU"
                        >PFIAB</orgName></gloss> Recommendation on <gloss target="#t_START_1"><rs
                            corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O" type="event">START</rs></gloss>
                    <rs corresp="recvMEtDFpnXkyj45" type="topic">Verification</rs> and <rs
                        corresp="recQ5xJqddmHqhjNl" type="topic">Arms Control</rs></item>
            </list>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Issue</p>
            <p>Should you sign the attached <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> which responds to
                the <gloss target="#t_PFIAB_1"><orgName corresp="recadxMxnHKQXZmiU"
                    >PFIAB</orgName></gloss> recommendations?<note n="2" place="foot"
                    xml:id="d40fn2">Printed as <ref target="#d41">Document 41</ref>.</note>
            </p>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Facts</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="recTv24KjXFdhanyt">Anne Armstrong</persName> has forwarded <gloss
                    target="#t_PFIAB_1"><orgName corresp="recadxMxnHKQXZmiU"
                >PFIAB</orgName></gloss>’s examination of the adequacy of the <rs
                    corresp="rec0tfPbYHg7imwab" type="topic">intelligence community</rs>’s
                capability and organization for assessing <gloss target="#t_SALT_1"><rs
                        corresp="rec6OIA4luUvtBKNn" type="event">SALT</rs></gloss>/<gloss
                    target="#t_START_1"><rs corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O" type="event"
                    >START</rs></gloss>
                <rs corresp="recMjLDCnI9cLa32M" type="topic">compliance</rs> issues (Tab C).<note
                    n="3" place="foot" xml:id="d40fn3">Attached but not printed. See <ref
                        target="#d38">Document 38</ref>.</note> Key <gloss target="#t_PFIAB_1"
                        ><orgName corresp="recadxMxnHKQXZmiU">PFIAB</orgName></gloss>
                recommendations include:</p>
            <p>—Creation of a high level policy mechanism to oversee review and assess all aspects
                of <rs corresp="recvMEtDFpnXkyj45" type="topic">verification</rs> and <rs
                    corresp="recMjLDCnI9cLa32M" type="topic">compliance</rs>, chaired by the
                Assistant to the President for National Security Affairs.</p>
            <p>—Creation of a “Red Team” to anticipate Soviet cheating scenarios.</p>
            <p>—The development of range of measured action responses short of treaty abrogation
                which the <placeName corresp="recxXt2KOngYAhHuL">US</placeName> could take if
                violations were detected.</p>
            <p>—Drafting of precise treaty language to prevent ambiguities and loopholes in <rs
                    corresp="recvMEtDFpnXkyj45" type="topic">verification</rs> of provisions.</p>
            <p>—A critical review of Soviet cover, concealment and deception (<gloss
                    target="#t_CCD_1">CCD</gloss>) actions related to strategic arms.</p>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Discussion</p>
            <p>The <gloss target="#t_PFIAB_1"><orgName corresp="recadxMxnHKQXZmiU"
                    >PFIAB</orgName></gloss> recommendations are sound. Some progress is being made,
                but the interagency process has not worked properly in the <rs
                    corresp="recvMEtDFpnXkyj45" type="topic">verification</rs> area. Creation of a
                high level Verification Committee reporting to the <gloss target="#t_NSC_1"><orgName
                        corresp="recft7WGb7Fww0wma">NSC</orgName></gloss> is a sine qua non for
                serious consideration of all aspects of <rs corresp="recMjLDCnI9cLa32M" type="topic"
                    >compliance</rs>. The attached <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> for your
                signature establishes the <rs corresp="recvMEtDFpnXkyj45" type="topic"
                    >Verification</rs> Committee.</p>
            <pb facs="0159" n="130" xml:id="pg_130"/>
            <p>A letter to <persName corresp="recTv24KjXFdhanyt">Anne Armstrong</persName>
                <note n="4" place="foot" xml:id="d40fn4">Printed as <ref target="#d42">Document
                        42</ref>.</note> acknowledges the recommendations, and requests that <gloss
                    target="#t_PFIAB_1"><orgName corresp="recadxMxnHKQXZmiU">PFIAB</orgName></gloss>
                undertake the review of Soviet <gloss target="#t_CCD_1">CCD</gloss> in cooperation
                with <persName corresp="rec7YPjp5UCcrZuXE">Bill Casey</persName>.</p>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Recommendation</p>
            <table cols="3">
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <hi rendition="simple_italic">OK</hi>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>
                        <hi rendition="simple_italic">No</hi>
                    </cell>
                    <cell/>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>________</cell>
                    <cell>________</cell>
                    <cell>1. That you sign the attached <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss>.<note
                            n="5" place="foot" xml:id="d40fn5">An unknown hand indicated approval on
                                <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Reagan</persName>’s
                            behalf.</note> (Tab A)</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell/>
                    <cell/>
                    <cell>2. That you sign the letter to <persName corresp="recTv24KjXFdhanyt">Anne
                            Armstrong</persName>.<note n="6" place="foot" xml:id="d40fn6">An unknown
                            hand indicated approval on <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq"
                                >Reagan</persName>’s behalf.</note> (Tab B)</cell>
                </row>
            </table>
        </body>
    </text>
